Access to the ICS machines is through secure shell &lt;tt&gt;ssh&lt;/tt&gt; to the host IP address 134.157.15.xx To connect via &lt;tt&gt;ssh&lt;/tt&gt;, you must have a ssh software (available in recent releases of Unix-based systems) and a connection to the campus network. On Windows operating systems, you can download a [http://www.filewatcher.com/m/SSHSecureShellClient-3.2.9.exe.5517312-0.html SSH Secure Shell Utility]. If you have a local system that runs an X Window client or server, you can run X applications remotely. You need to know your LDAP login name and password.
&nbsp;
== Connection to SGi systems ==
&nbsp;
The following procedure will establish a connection to one of the two front-end servers (choice is automatic).
&nbsp;
===Opening a connection===
&nbsp;
To open a connection to MeSU, first open a terminal and at the command prompt type
[code language="css"] ssh loginLDAP@mesu.dsi.upmc.fr [/code]
&nbsp;
ssh -X loginLDAP@mesu.dsi.upmc.fr
The -X option allows X windows applications running on the SGIs to be forwarded to your local machine.In order to enable X forwarding from the SGI to a local Mac OS X machine, the &lt;tt&gt;ssh&lt;/tt&gt; command has to be typed from a X11 terminal.
=== Logging in ===
&nbsp;
When the &lt;tt&gt;ssh&lt;/tt&gt; connection is established you will be prompted for your password. You can save your &lt;tt&gt;ssh keys&lt;/tt&gt; on the server in the directory &lt;tt&gt;/home/login_ldap/.ssh/&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;b&gt;Note&lt;/b&gt;: if you want to get rid of Man in the Middle connection problems, edit the file &lt;tt&gt;.ssh/config&lt;/tt&gt; in your home directory and append the following lines: &lt;pre class="code"&gt; Host mesu.dsi.upmc.fr StrictHostKeyChecking no UserKnownHostsFile=/dev/null LogLevel QUIET &lt;/pre&gt;
=== Logging out ===
To leave the system, please check that all your files are closed and all jobs have been terminated. Then enter: &lt;pre class="command"&gt;exit&lt;/pre&gt;
